Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
create_rc_corner(25.10)                                create_rc_corner(25.10)

Name
       create_rc_corner  - Creates a named RC corner object that can be refer-
       enced later when creating a delay calculation corner object

Syntax
       create_rc_corner

       [-help]

       [-T <temperatureValue>]

       [-cap_table <capTableFile>]

       -name <rcCornerName>

       [-postRoute_cap {<capFactor1 capFactor2 capFactor3>}]

       [-postRoute_clkcap {<capFactor1 capFactor2 capFactor3>}]

       [-postRoute_clkres {<resFactor1 resFactor2 resFactor3>}]

       [-postRoute_res {<resFactor1 resFactor2 resFactor3>}]

       [-postRoute_xcap {<xcapFactor1 xcapFactor2 xcapFactor3>}]

       [-preRoute_cap <capFactor>]

       [-preRoute_clkcap <capFactor>]

       [-preRoute_clkres <resFactor>]

       [-preRoute_res <resFactor>]

       [-qx_tech_file <fileName>]

       [-thru_substrate_cell_subckt_file <fileName>]

       [-via_variation_file <viaVariationFile>]

       Creates a named RC corner object that can be referenced later when cre-
       ating a delay calculation corner object. An RC corner  object  provides
       the software with all of the information necessary to properly extract,
       annotate, and use the RCs for delay calculation.

       Note:  You  must  use the RC corner scaling attributes when running the
       software in multi-mode multi-corner analysis mode. Use the setExtractR-
       CMode command to set the extraction mode for all RC corner  objects  in
       the design.

       Note: In multi-mode multi-corner mode, only the default RC corners cre-
       ated  by the software inherit the derating factor values defined in the
       configuration file.

       You can set different postroute scale factors for the postroute  engine
       variants by specifying them as duplets and triplets. For example,

       <resFactor1> <resFactor2> <resFactor3>

       Where:

              * Single  value:  If you specify one value, the scale factor ap-
                plies to effort level low. Scale factor value of 1 is used for
                medium and high by default.

              * Duplet: If you specify two values, the first value is used for
                effort level low and the second  value  is  used  for  medium.
                Scale factor value of 1 is used for high by default.

              * Triplet:  If you specify three values, the first value is used
                for effort level low, the second value is used for medium, and
                the third value is used for high.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation  for  each  create_rc_corner parameter. For a detailed
              description of the command and all of its  parameters,  use  the
              man command: man create_rc_corner.

       -cap_table <capTableFile>
              Specifies the capacitance table to use for extraction when using
              this RC corner.

              Default:  The  Innovus extraction system uses internal rules for
              extracting resistances and capacitances.

       -preRoute_cap <capFactor>
              Specifies the capacitance scale factor for RC Extraction in pre-
              Route mode.

              Default: 1.0

       -preRoute_clkcap <capFactor>
              Specifies the scale factor for capacitance of clock nets in pre-
              Route mode.

              Default: 0

              When this parameter is not specified, the value  specified  with
              the -postRoute_cap parameter is used for preRoute extraction.

              When  specified,  this  parameter  overrides the value specified
              with the -postRoute_cap parameter for clock nets.

       -preRoute_clkres <resFactor>
              Specifies the scale factor for resistance of clock nets in  pre-
              rRoute mode.

              Default: 0

              When  this  parameter is not specified, the value specified with
              the -postRoute_res parameter is used for preRoute extraction.

              When specified, this parameter  overrides  the  value  specified
              with the -postRoute_res parameter for clock nets.

       -preRoute_res <resFactor>
              Specifies  the resistance scale factor for RC extraction in pre-
              Route mode.

       -postRoute_cap {<capFactor1 capFactor2 capFactor3>}
              Specifies the capacitance scale  factor  for  RC  extraction  in
              postRoute mode.

              Default: 1.0

       -postRoute_clkcap {<capFactor1 capFactor2 capFactor3>}
              Specifies  the scale factor for capacitance of clock nets in the
              postRoute extraction mode.

              Default: 0

              When this parameter is not specified, the value  specified  with
              the  -postRoute_cap  parameter is used for postRoute extraction.
              When specified, this parameter  overrides  the  value  specified
              with the -postRoute_cap parameter.

       -postRoute_clkres {<resFactor1 resFactor2 resFactor3>}
              Specifies  the  scale factor for resistance of clock nets in the
              postroute extraction mode.

              Default: 0

              When this parameter is not specified, the value  specified  with
              the  -postRoute_res  parameter is used for postRoute extraction.
              When specified, this parameter  overrides  the  value  specified
              with the -postRoute_res parameter for clock nets.

       -postRoute_res {<resFactor1 resFactor2 resFactor3>}
              Specifies the resistance scale factor for RC extraction in post-
              route mode.

       -postRoute_xcap {<xcapFactor1 xcapFactor2 xcapFactor3>}
              Specifies  the  coupling capacitance scale factor for RC extrac-
              tion in postroute mode.

              Default: 1.0

       -name <rcCornerName>
              Specifies the name for the RC corner object being  created.  You
              can  choose  any  name for an RC corner object, but it is recom-
              mended that you use a name that can be easily recognized as  re-
              ferring to a specific RC corner (for example, rc-min, rc-max, c-
              min, c-max, and so on).

       -qx_tech_file <fileName>
              Specifies the name of the Quantus technology (.tch) file used by
              TQuantus/IQuantus or Quantus sign-off RC extraction.

              The  technology  file  is generated by TechGen, a built-in func-
              tionality of Quantus. For most technologies  you  can  get  this
              file  from  technology  vendors.  For  technologies that are not
              available through the technology vendors, you enter the fabrica-
              tion process information into an ASCII-format interconnect tech-
              nology (ICT) input file. The ICT file is then used as  input  to
              IceCaps, which in turn generates the technology file.

              For more information on creating the ICT files, see the chapter,
              "Creating the ICT File", in the Innovus User Guide.

       -T <rcTemperatureValue>
              Specifies the temperature, in units of Celsius, to use to derate
              resistance values.

              Use this parameter when you want to override the default temper-
              ature specified in the capacitance table or the Quantus technol-
              ogy file.

              Note:  The software does not require that the temperature speci-
              fied by the PVT operating condition  at  the  delay  calculation
              corner  level  be  the  same as the RC nominal or user-specified
              temperature value.

              Default: The Innovus extraction system uses the default tempera-
              ture of 25 degrees Celsius, unless it is overridden by  the  ca-
              pacitance table or the Quantus technology file.

       -thru_substrate_cell_subckt_file <fileName>
              Specifies  file  containing subcircuit models for thru substrate
              cells. These cells are special via cells that allow to  go  from
              frontside layers to backside layers and vice versa.

       -via_variation_file <viaVariationFile>
              Specifies  a  file for modeling via variation. The VIA variation
              file lists up all the VIA layer  names  with  the  corresponding
              multiplier. Each RC corner can have its own VIA variation file.

              For example:

              create_rc_corner

                  -name rcCornerName1 \

                  -via_variation_file viaVariationFileName1

              create_rc_corner

                  -name rcCornerName2 \

                  -via_variation_file viaVariationFileName2

Examples
              * The  following  command  creates  an RC corner called rc-cbest
                that uses the capacitance table myTech_4_bc.CapTbl,  and  der-
                ates the resistance values based on the temperature of 50 Cel-
                sius:

                create_rc_corner  -name rc-cbest -cap_table myTech.4_bc.CapTbl
                -T 50

Related Information
